
Compiling details :
________________________________________________________________________________

The compiler first calls the pre-processor. 
- Pre-processor :
  - includes libraries/functions indicated by the directives.
  - <angular brackets> suggest that the library is in /usr/include . 
    Use "double quotes" instead to show that it's a local custom library just for this program. 

Then it converts the source code into objects files.
- Object file :
  - the source code in machine language form, used for generating the binary.
  - Every implementation file (.c) should have its respective object file. 

The compiler then calls the linker.
- Linker :
  - creates the binary. 
________________________________________________________________________________

Compiling broken up : 

- Just generate the object files : 
$ gcc 	 -c	...	-o    prog.o	    prog.c	...

- Invoke the linker (use the object files to generate the binary) : 
$ gcc 	     	    	-o    prog        prog.o 
________________________________________________________________________________

Object face :
- all the object files to be generated. 

Link face :
- all the linker flags to be used. 

